cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI 

This paper deals with 3D reconstruction of dynamic objects captured by a single camera, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of shape-from-shading (SfS) is a key component of the proposed approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with tracking and reconstruction of dynamic objects, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics). The use of SfS and modeling of specularities and shading could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
